<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Exercise Gallery</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 0 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
        }
        .exercise {
            margin-bottom: 40px;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        .exercise img {
            float: left;
            margin-right: 20px;
            max-width: 200px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .exercise-content {
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        .exercise-content h2 {
            margin-top: 0;
        }
        .exercise-content p {
            margin-top: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Exercise Gallery</h1>
        
        <div class="exercise">
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/200" alt="Exercise 1">
            <div class="exercise-content">
                <h2>Push-ups</h2>
                <p>Push-ups are a great bodyweight exercise that work your chest, shoulders, triceps, and core muscles.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="exercise">
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/200" alt="Exercise 2">
            <div class="exercise-content">
                <h2>Squats</h2>
                <p>Squats are a compound exercise that targets your quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and lower back.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="exercise">
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/200" alt="Exercise 3">
            <div class="exercise-content">
                <h2>Plank</h2>
                <p>The plank is an isometric exercise that strengthens your core muscles, including your abs, back, and shoulders.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Add more exercises as needed -->

    </div>
</body>
</html>
